      <p>You don't need to drop $200 on work boots to get reliable protection on a construction site. Some of the best-rated boots on Amazon cost under $100 — and they still deliver steel toe safety, slip resistance, and all-day comfort.</p>
      <p>The key is knowing which budget boots actually hold up. We've combed through the reviews, safety certifications, and real-world feedback from tradespeople to find the affordable work boots that won't let you down. Here are the best budget work boots under $100 available right now.</p>

      <h2>What to Look for in Budget Work Boots</h2>
      <p>When you're spending under $100, you have to be smart about what matters most. Here's what to prioritize:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>ASTM certification is non-negotiable.</strong> Even at a lower price point, make sure the boot carries ASTM F2413-18 rating for impact and compression protection. Never compromise on safety ratings.</li>
        <li><strong>Slip resistance matters more than waterproofing.</strong> In the budget category, getting a truly waterproof boot under $100 is rare. Focus on slip resistance — it's more critical for daily safety on most sites.</li>
        <li><strong>Read reviews for break-in comfort.</strong> Budget boots that take weeks to break in aren't worth the savings. Look for boots with multiple reviews mentioning "no break-in needed" or "comfortable out of the box."</li>
        <li><strong>Synthetic uppers save weight and cost.</strong> While full-grain leather is premium, synthetic and split-leather uppers in budget boots are lighter and still durable enough for typical construction work.</li>
      </ul>

